21:43.034 --> 21:45.571
This is good work. Digging tools...

21:46.338 --> 21:48.045
The tesla coil...

21:48.106 --> 21:49.517
Electrical equipment...

21:50.308 --> 21:55.090
And who has a Zom-bake sale in the
middle of nowhere, during a rainstorm?

21:55.547 --> 21:56.548
Ooh! Brownie!

21:56.615 --> 21:59.459
Don't eat that. I checked.
Yeah, it's, like, 90% dirt.

22:00.952 --> 22:02.659
What could they possibly be up to?

22:04.489 --> 22:09.199
I feel terrible asking,
but can you keep watching them?

22:10.896 --> 22:12.603
It's what I do best.

22:12.664 --> 22:14.644
Just please be careful.

22:15.300 --> 22:17.405
I don't want you to end up
in any kind of danger.

22:19.838 --> 22:20.873
Whoa!

22:23.808 --> 22:25.385
You know, like now, for instance.

22:32.584 --> 22:33.654
Twyla!

22:33.718 --> 22:35.163
I'm okay. I...

23:09.821 --> 23:13.198
You saved me, Frankie. Thank you.

23:13.258 --> 23:14.362
Don't mention it.

23:16.695 --> 23:20.006
Frankie, um, are you okay?

23:21.466 --> 23:24.174
I'm all right.
A little lightning never hurt anybody.

23:24.603 --> 23:26.674
I mean, never hurt a Stein anyway.

23:27.239 --> 23:30.777
But from now on,
what do you say we meet indoors?

23:32.844 --> 23:35.484
Huh. That's never happened before.

23:35.547 --> 23:37.788
Well, that was a lot of lightning.

23:38.250 --> 23:40.355
You're sure you don't need some help?

23:41.019 --> 23:42.225
No, I'm fine.

23:42.621 --> 23:45.564
Listen, we're having another
ghouls' night tonight upstairs.

23:45.624 --> 23:46.625
You want to come?

23:46.691 --> 23:51.002
I think I've already had more
excitement than I can handle.

23:51.062 --> 23:52.063
Thanks, though.

23:52.130 --> 23:56.044
Okay, well, if you change your mind,
you've got my iCoffin number.

24:10.015 --> 24:12.052
Huh? Hmm.

24:30.435 --> 24:31.743
Good morning, Twyla!

24:31.803 --> 24:33.840
That was quite a storm last night, huh?

24:33.905 --> 24:37.751
Yeah. Um, that electricity thing
still happening to you?

24:38.076 --> 24:41.148
It's no big deal.
In fact, I woke up full of energy.

24:41.446 --> 24:43.221
Hmm. Right.

24:43.281 --> 24:46.956
Hey, so I'm going to go spy
on that Zom-bake sale.

24:47.018 --> 24:50.829
I'm pretty sure those guys
are hiding something.

24:50.889 --> 24:52.527
Be sure to call me when you find out.

24:52.591 --> 24:53.865
Of course. I will.

24:54.459 --> 24:56.166
Well, at least it's a nice day.

27:02.870 --> 27:06.643
Hey, guys. The creepateria
has brains for lunch today.

27:06.707 --> 27:09.003
- Brains?
- Brains?

27:09.094 --> 27:11.299
- Brains? Brains?
- Brains? Brains?

27:26.010 --> 27:27.148
Get back to work!

27:27.212 --> 27:29.214
You can sleep when you're dead.

27:29.280 --> 27:32.090
Or, well, you know what I mean.

27:32.150 --> 27:36.860
No more breaks until all
that electricity is in there.

27:37.489 --> 27:41.904
Frankie's science project?
What are they up to?

28:20.231 --> 28:21.471
Come on, ghouls.

28:25.170 --> 28:28.708
I don't care what your boss said, Rene.

28:28.773 --> 28:31.750
That price is outrageous
for cuticle scrapers.

28:32.911 --> 28:34.285
Hey, be careful with that.

28:34.345 --> 28:37.053
Aunt Nephthys hates to be woken up.

28:37.115 --> 28:41.392
Rene, I wasn't born yesterday.
I was born 6,000 years ago.

28:42.754 --> 28:45.792
Don't worry about how that's possible.
Worry about my cuticles.

28:45.857 --> 28:47.832
Hey, mate. Where does this go?

28:47.892 --> 28:49.701
Oh, just over there
by the hair dryers for now.

28:50.061 --> 28:51.062
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

28:51.796 --> 28:52.797
Heel!

28:52.897 --> 28:54.638
That is not a toy.

28:57.335 --> 28:58.336
Ha! Got you!

29:02.207 --> 29:04.687
Hi, this is Twyla. Please leave a message.

29:04.776 --> 29:06.915
Come on, Twyla, why aren't you answering?

29:16.421 --> 29:17.525
Hey, Cleo.

29:17.589 --> 29:20.365
I'm sorry. I know we
have a lot going on here,

29:20.425 --> 29:22.462
but I have to step out for a few.

29:22.560 --> 29:23.868
Everything all right, Frankie?

29:24.362 --> 29:26.433
It's nothing I can't handle on my own.

29:26.497 --> 29:29.000
I just need to check on somebody.

29:29.067 --> 29:30.740
Oh, do whatever you need to do.

29:30.802 --> 29:32.744
Lagoona and I will be fine over here.

29:32.804 --> 29:34.712
We have everything under control.

29:36.808 --> 29:38.287
Excuse me.

29:42.947 --> 29:45.450
Welcome to the very first jam session

29:45.516 --> 29:48.459
of Raythe and the Silent Screams.

29:48.519 --> 29:50.692
And a one and a two and a...

29:51.489 --> 29:53.298
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Wait. Wait. Hold up.

29:53.358 --> 29:57.500
We're not calling the band
"Raythe and the Something Something."

29:57.562 --> 30:01.806
Skelly said we were gonna
be The Rolling Bones.

30:06.004 --> 30:08.780
We should name the band
something more powerful.

30:08.840 --> 30:11.787
What about Thunder and Frightening?

30:13.144 --> 30:17.889
No, I like Raythe and the Silent Screams.

30:17.949 --> 30:19.519
Now let's jam.

30:19.617 --> 30:23.394
Um, you can't just name the band
after yourself, Raythe.

30:23.454 --> 30:27.332
One, I'm the lead singer.
Two, it's an awesome name.

30:27.392 --> 30:29.133
Three, let's jam.

30:29.627 --> 30:33.507
Oh! What about Ghoulish Intentions?

30:33.698 --> 30:37.041
Ooh! Ooh, ooh, ooh! What about
Raythe and the Silent Screams?

30:37.101 --> 30:38.443
Dude, you don't just name the band after you!

30:38.503 --> 30:39.911
What don't you like about
Ghoulish Intentions?

30:39.971 --> 30:42.679
This is a team effort. It's a band.

30:42.774 --> 30:44.879
That's the worst name
in the history of names.

30:46.644 --> 30:48.248
- Whoa!
- Okay.

30:49.881 --> 30:53.351
Look, I'm still the new ghoul here,

30:53.418 --> 30:56.627
but I know this isn't
what Monster High is about.

30:57.055 --> 31:01.333
We didn't start this band to argue
over something as silly as a name.

31:01.893 --> 31:05.932
We're here to make awesome music together.

31:06.798 --> 31:08.744
Monster music.

31:09.600 --> 31:11.943
Silvi's right.
We shouldn't be fighting like this.

31:12.003 --> 31:13.004
My bad.

31:13.071 --> 31:14.744
I'm sorry.

31:15.740 --> 31:19.480
Besides, the band should be
called The Howling Army.

31:20.578 --> 31:21.579
What?

31:21.646 --> 31:23.182
- This is a team effort, man.
- Hey!

31:23.247 --> 31:24.954
- I know what I'm talking about.
- No! You wanna get...

31:25.016 --> 31:27.519
That's the worst name
in the history of names.

31:27.585 --> 31:29.792
The Rolling Bones. Come on!

31:31.822 --> 31:33.524
No peeking.

31:33.758 --> 31:36.295
Okay, ghouls. Here goes.

31:36.661 --> 31:37.702
Clawdeen!

31:37.762 --> 31:39.764
- I knew you could do it, Clawdeen!
- Creeparific.

31:39.831 --> 31:41.333
You really like them?

31:41.432 --> 31:44.641
Mmm-hmm. Oh! I can't wait to wear
these at the salon opening tonight.

31:44.702 --> 31:47.545
- They are fangtastic!
- Thanks.

31:47.605 --> 31:50.916
All my inspiration was thanks
to you and the ghouls.

31:51.542 --> 31:54.485
But I still think there's something missing.

31:54.545 --> 31:57.151
Hey, ghouls, sorry I'm late.
I just got this big burst of energy.

31:57.215 --> 31:59.354
So I decided to walk
around the school 14times,

31:59.417 --> 32:01.727
you know, after I did
the Humanology reading assignment.

32:02.186 --> 32:03.893
Um, who broke Frankie?

32:03.955 --> 32:06.697
And then I did the rest of the reading
for the next two semesters.

32:07.825 --> 32:09.801
Hey, look at that, Clawdeen.
Those looks are so voltageous.

32:09.861 --> 32:10.862
I knew you could do it.

32:10.928 --> 32:13.371
Hey, do I sound like I'm talking fast?
I'm talking fast, aren't I?

32:15.033 --> 32:17.707
Frankie, Frankie! Slow down!

32:17.769 --> 32:19.806
How many mummy mochas did you drink, huh?

32:20.204 --> 32:21.674
Why, I've never been so full of energy.

32:21.739 --> 32:25.077
That's a great idea. I'll go get us all
some mummy mochas. I'll be right back.

32:26.811 --> 32:30.953
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa. No.
Why don't we sit down for a minute?

32:33.584 --> 32:36.895
It's like there's too much
electricity inside her.

32:37.321 --> 32:38.891
She's all amped up.

32:39.624 --> 32:41.035
Oh, no! My dress!

32:46.130 --> 32:47.165
Wow!

32:52.537 --> 32:54.312
Amazing!

33:03.014 --> 33:04.994
This is what my outfits were missing.

33:05.283 --> 33:09.095
A power station salon
deserves electric fashion.

33:14.459 --> 33:17.839
I'm electric, doing my thing

33:18.296 --> 33:22.038
I'm electric, I'm gonna light it, light it up

33:22.100 --> 33:25.809
I'm electric, sparks of lightning

33:25.870 --> 33:29.680
I'm electric, I'm gonna light it, light it up

33:29.740 --> 33:32.579
I'm electric, can you feel the magic?
Like lightning

33:33.144 --> 33:36.949
I'm electric, I'm electric
I'm gonna light it, light it up

33:37.014 --> 33:40.317
I'm electric, can you feel the magic?
Like lightning

33:40.785 --> 33:44.429
I'm electric, I'm electric
I'm gonna light it, light it up

33:44.489 --> 33:46.297
Shine, shine, shine, everybody got a light

33:46.357 --> 33:48.564
Got to work your dream
and show me that starlight

33:48.626 --> 33:50.264
Every season, I'll touch that...

33:50.328 --> 33:52.436
From your cap to your sneakers
Baby, it's a keeper

33:52.496 --> 33:55.968
Be a leader, don't be a follower
Wear it like a star and everybody holla

33:56.033 --> 33:57.808
When I walk in a room, man,
people be grooving

33:57.869 --> 33:59.789
Who's that girl? It's me, I'm illumin'

34:03.875 --> 34:07.080
I'm electric, can you feel the magic?
Like lightning

34:07.612 --> 34:11.181
I'm electric, I'm electric
I'm gonna light it, light it up

34:11.248 --> 34:14.755
I'm electric, can you feel the magic?
Like lightning

34:15.286 --> 34:19.297
I'm electric, I'm electric
I'm gonna light it, light it up

34:25.295 --> 34:31.371
Presenting Miss Clawdeen
Wolf's Fierce Electric Fashions!

34:33.237 --> 34:35.079
- Look at those ghouls.
- Check it out.

34:35.139 --> 34:36.947
Shock and awesome!

34:37.275 --> 34:40.347
- Shock and awesome.
- Aw, that looks great!

34:40.777 --> 34:42.348
- Awesome.
- Hey, check that out.

34:42.679 --> 34:43.715
That's cool.

34:43.781 --> 34:45.123
- Look at those ghouls.
- Oh, my goodness!

34:45.183 --> 34:47.219
- Bright lights!
- Wow! Check it out!

34:47.284 --> 34:49.856
It's like a party but also a dress!

34:49.920 --> 34:52.161
- So cool!
- Can I get one? Can I get one?

34:52.223 --> 34:53.395
Oh, my gosh. Get me one.

34:53.456 --> 34:54.458
Sweet.

34:56.260 --> 34:57.967
We're really turning some heads.

34:59.230 --> 35:00.231
Hey, Clawdeen.

35:00.298 --> 35:02.972
You look, uh... I mean,
you and the ghouls are like...

35:03.034 --> 35:04.876
You're very, uh...

35:04.936 --> 35:06.979
Did I mention that we started a band?

35:07.705 --> 35:09.343
Thank you, Raythe.

35:16.180 --> 35:18.155
Frankie? Are you okay?

35:18.416 --> 35:22.455
It still feels like there's
a little electricity left in there.

35:23.254 --> 35:24.392
Maybe I can...

35:25.356 --> 35:26.357
Whoa!

35:32.630 --> 35:33.631
Watch out!

35:35.666 --> 35:36.667
Look out! Whoa!

35:42.273 --> 35:43.614
Aww!

35:43.674 --> 35:44.982
Adorbes.

35:45.042 --> 35:46.282
What is it?

35:46.344 --> 35:47.414
Znap!

35:47.478 --> 35:49.116
I guess it's a Znap.

35:49.513 --> 35:50.583
Znap! Znap!

35:51.082 --> 35:53.858
Well, it is very nice to meet you, Znap.

35:55.753 --> 35:56.788
Ooh.

35:57.188 --> 35:59.130
Maybe we can just bow.

35:59.190 --> 36:00.669
Znap, Znap, Znap!

36:00.758 --> 36:02.601
- Hmm. Oh!
- Znap!

36:06.998 --> 36:07.999
Cool.

36:08.399 --> 36:11.275
So, ghouls, now that we have
our fierce new looks,

36:11.335 --> 36:13.177
what do you say we head
over to the power station

36:13.237 --> 36:15.114
and see if Cleo's ready for tonight?

36:17.375 --> 36:20.254
Let me catch up with you.
I have to check on something first.

36:29.787 --> 36:31.926
Twyla? Are you here?

36:37.595 --> 36:39.734
Oh, come on, Twyla. Where are you?

36:43.701 --> 36:45.180
Something's not right.

36:47.972 --> 36:49.610
Hello? Twyla? Are you there?

36:49.674 --> 36:51.119
Ugh. Wrong number.

37:05.723 --> 37:07.964
Are you still fiddling with that thing?

37:08.025 --> 37:09.595
I thought you'd be done by now.

37:11.295 --> 37:12.399
Uh...

37:12.930 --> 37:14.000
Uh...

37:16.801 --> 37:17.905
Uh...

37:33.551 --> 37:35.690
Is it finished? Can we get started?

37:39.023 --> 37:40.865
Ugh! Finally!

37:40.925 --> 37:43.064
I know what you're up to, Moanica.

37:43.127 --> 37:44.697
Oh, really?

37:44.762 --> 37:46.604
You're stealing all the electricity.

37:46.664 --> 37:51.204
I figured it out. I mean,
we're underneath the power station.

38:14.692 --> 38:15.796
Hmm.

38:18.162 --> 38:19.368
Uh-huh.

38:34.345 --> 38:36.347
You're going to use Frankie's science project

38:36.414 --> 38:39.327
to take all the electricity
out of the power grid.

38:39.817 --> 38:44.891
Mira! And they say Frankie
is the ghoul with all the brains.

38:44.955 --> 38:45.990
Brain?

38:47.658 --> 38:50.832
No, there aren't any brains.

38:52.730 --> 38:56.678
You know, you can steal the electricity
to ruin the big salon opening,

38:57.701 --> 39:00.944
but it won't stop those ghouls
from following their dream.

39:02.606 --> 39:08.716
I don't care about their little
"salon" or their "misguided" dream.

39:08.779 --> 39:10.918
Ruining that is just a bonus.

39:11.615 --> 39:17.122
Professor Dracula said that Normies
are afraid of the dark, right?

39:17.455 --> 39:23.133
So when we use this bad boy
to take all of their electricity...

39:23.594 --> 39:25.369
Total darkness!

39:25.896 --> 39:28.873
And when the Normies are good and scared,

39:28.933 --> 39:31.004
the Zomboys and I

39:31.068 --> 39:34.777
will go out into the world and show them

39:34.839 --> 39:39.845
how truly scarifying we monsters can be!

39:40.344 --> 39:41.755
Right, Zomboys?

39:44.982 --> 39:46.393
Hey! Be scary!

39:53.657 --> 39:58.766
This is the Night of the Zomboys!

40:38.369 --> 40:39.541
Impressive...

40:40.037 --> 40:41.038
Fail.

40:47.111 --> 40:49.148
What was that?

40:49.213 --> 40:53.093
I thought you Zomboys said
you knew what you were doing.

40:56.654 --> 40:58.660
Worthless!

41:00.958 --> 41:03.302
I've gotta get some air.

41:14.471 --> 41:15.779
Moanica.

41:15.839 --> 41:17.079
Frankie.

41:17.141 --> 41:20.486
You wouldn't happen to know
where Twyla is, would you?

41:21.078 --> 41:25.458
Who, me? How should I know where
that shadow ghoul likes to sneak?

41:25.950 --> 41:28.225
If you do know where Twyla is...

41:28.285 --> 41:29.286
I'll find out.

41:31.021 --> 41:32.329
Znap, Znap, Znap.

41:33.324 --> 41:34.732
"I'll find out."

41:43.634 --> 41:45.545
Yes, Frankie.

41:46.537 --> 41:48.778
You'll find out where Twyla is.

41:49.473 --> 41:51.419
Time for plan B.

41:56.647 --> 41:59.150
Release the Boogey girl. She's free to go.

42:01.352 --> 42:05.198
No, I'm...  I'm not mad at you anymore.

42:06.023 --> 42:07.832
You're still my Zomboys.

42:11.161 --> 42:14.538
Yes, we can get ice cream after
we finish the Night of the Zomboys.

42:38.122 --> 42:39.897
All right. So it's settled.

42:39.957 --> 42:42.900
The name of the band
is Howling Thunder and Frightening

42:42.960 --> 42:48.433
featuring Raythe and Deuce
and The Rolling Bones and Woolee.

42:50.134 --> 42:52.740
You know there's no way
that's going to fit on a T-shirt.

42:52.803 --> 42:54.476
Hey. Howling Thunder and Frightening

42:54.538 --> 42:56.575
featuring Raythe and Deuce
and The Rolling Bones and Woolee

42:56.640 --> 42:59.280
isn't about T-shirts and making money.

42:59.343 --> 43:02.017
It's about our message
and monster alternative.

43:03.347 --> 43:06.223
Um, monster alternative?

43:06.283 --> 43:09.730
I thought we were going
to be playing heavy metal!

43:11.355 --> 43:16.327
No. HTFFRDATRB's and Woolee
is a Monster Alternative band.

43:16.393 --> 43:17.497
Guys. Guys.

43:17.561 --> 43:20.872
Doesn't it make more sense
for a monster band to play goth rock?

43:21.298 --> 43:24.939
Great, now we don't even agree on
the kind of music we're gonna play?

43:25.002 --> 43:27.278
Bonesy, Skelly, what about you guys?

43:31.542 --> 43:34.386
Smooth jazz? Only my mom likes smooth jazz!

43:34.978 --> 43:37.185
Metal is the only cool kind of music.

43:37.648 --> 43:38.888
- How many times do I have to say it?
- No.

43:38.949 --> 43:42.520
- Monster alternative for sure.
- Goth is totally now!

43:43.220 --> 43:44.221
What? Oh, come on.

43:56.600 --> 43:57.601
Hey, Frankie!

43:58.936 --> 44:00.574
Twyla!

44:00.671 --> 44:03.277
Where have you been?
I've been looking all over for...

44:03.373 --> 44:06.815
It's Moanica. She had her Zomboys
dig a tunnel under the power station.

44:06.877 --> 44:08.447
Znap! Znap!

44:08.545 --> 44:09.649
What's that?

44:09.713 --> 44:10.885
Znap, Znap.

44:10.948 --> 44:14.589
I'll explain later.
Why on Earth are they digging a tunnel?

44:14.651 --> 44:17.995
Because she wants to steal
all the electricity, all the light...

44:18.055 --> 44:19.466
Frankie?

44:19.690 --> 44:22.637
Clawdeen. What are you doing here?

44:23.427 --> 44:24.835
I came looking for you.

44:24.895 --> 44:29.236
I can't have our big salon opening without
one of my best ghoul friends there with me.

44:29.299 --> 44:31.472
- No, you shouldn't go back there now...
- Clawdeen.

44:31.535 --> 44:34.478
Your dream is becoming a reality tonight.

44:34.538 --> 44:36.540
You go make sure everything is perfect.

44:36.607 --> 44:37.881
I'll meet you there soon.

44:37.941 --> 44:40.217
Okay. But don't be late.

44:40.644 --> 44:44.488
Oh! I'm so excited, I can't stop howling.

44:50.487 --> 44:53.366
Now, where is this tunnel?

45:01.965 --> 45:05.606
Hmm. That's odd.
There are usually Zomboys here.

45:09.573 --> 45:12.449
Frankie, I know you want
to take care of this on your own,

45:12.509 --> 45:15.853
but listen, that cavern
is swarming with Zomboys.

45:15.913 --> 45:19.224
I am more than capable of
outsmarting a few Zomboys.

45:19.917 --> 45:20.918
Znap!

45:20.984 --> 45:23.260
That salon means everything to Clawdeen.

45:23.554 --> 45:25.761
I'm not letting Moanica ruin her big night.

45:27.157 --> 45:28.158
Okay.

45:29.726 --> 45:30.727
Znap!

45:34.198 --> 45:36.542
Fine, then I'm coming with you.

45:36.967 --> 45:39.948
- So how far down does this go?
- A long way.

45:40.504 --> 45:44.179
It's really dark.
Good thing I'm my own light source.

45:47.945 --> 45:49.887
Hello. Hello, everyone.

45:49.947 --> 45:53.724
Thank you. Thank you all
for coming to our grand opening.

45:54.318 --> 45:58.095
I'd like to introduce Clawdeen Wolf,

45:58.155 --> 46:00.328
up-and-coming style genius.

46:03.660 --> 46:06.038
Welcome to Fierce!

46:06.163 --> 46:07.733
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

46:09.666 --> 46:10.804
This is amazing.

46:10.868 --> 46:12.745
I love the whole monster theme here.

46:13.470 --> 46:15.143
Check out the styling chairs.

46:15.205 --> 46:16.206
Pretty cool.

46:16.273 --> 46:18.651
- Yeah, it's really, out there, you know?
- Great colors.

46:21.311 --> 46:22.786
Whoa! They got a DJ.

46:22.846 --> 46:25.249
- This track is fresh.
- I love it.

46:25.315 --> 46:27.124
I would give this place an 11 out of 10.

46:27.184 --> 46:29.593
Their monster makeup is so realistic!

46:29.653 --> 46:32.963
Forget their makeup.
Did you see those outfits?

46:33.023 --> 46:35.332
They said this was a mummy mocha. Clever.

46:35.392 --> 46:38.998
- Can you do my hair like a werewolf?
- Wow! Look at my monster hair.

46:39.062 --> 46:40.166
Super stylish.

46:40.230 --> 46:42.904
- It's Tash!
- She got a monster makeover.

46:42.966 --> 46:44.604
Oh, that is so cool.

46:44.668 --> 46:46.113
That looks amazing.

46:46.403 --> 46:47.507
Oh, man.

46:47.671 --> 46:49.548
Did you see they have a fog machine?

46:50.741 --> 46:53.050
Check out my hair. This is awesome.

46:53.110 --> 46:56.216
I'm telling all my friends
about their monster style.

47:04.087 --> 47:05.964
Are you sure this looks good?

47:06.523 --> 47:10.096
Absolutely. It makes you look
at least 10,000 years younger.

47:10.761 --> 47:12.798
Uh, I'm not so sure about that...

47:13.463 --> 47:16.603
Hey! Love the new look, Dracula.

47:17.467 --> 47:19.309
Well, what do you know!

47:19.369 --> 47:20.814
So do I!

47:29.112 --> 47:31.989
I'm very proud of you, Clawdeen.

47:32.049 --> 47:33.653
Thanks, Mom.

47:33.717 --> 47:34.718
Something wrong?

47:34.785 --> 47:36.822
Frankie should be here.

47:36.887 --> 47:38.862
Just wondering where she is.

47:38.922 --> 47:41.798
I'm sure she's around here somewhere.

47:41.858 --> 47:43.769
Could you?

48:05.615 --> 48:07.993
Wait! There's lots of Zomboys up ahead.

48:10.787 --> 48:12.528
Seems pretty quiet.

48:19.396 --> 48:20.397
Znap?

48:22.032 --> 48:23.136
Huh?

48:31.274 --> 48:32.844
Frankie!

48:32.909 --> 48:34.388
Be careful!

48:46.089 --> 48:47.295
Znap!

48:48.124 --> 48:49.861
- Let go!
- Znap!

48:53.797 --> 48:57.210
So, what do you think?

48:58.702 --> 48:59.703
Frankie?

48:59.770 --> 49:02.478
I think you ruined my science project!

49:02.773 --> 49:03.877
Oh.

49:04.041 --> 49:07.853
I'm about to ruin much more than that.

49:09.179 --> 49:12.354
I'm taking this whole thing apart
before it can do any more damage.

49:12.416 --> 49:13.890
I don't think so.

49:13.950 --> 49:17.261
It's time for the Night of the Zomboys.

49:19.856 --> 49:22.496
Time for the Normies to be afraid.

49:22.559 --> 49:26.769
And they will be,
when I shut off all the lights!

49:27.931 --> 49:30.571
There are billions of watts
of energy in that power grid.

49:31.034 --> 49:32.308
Obviously there was no way

49:32.369 --> 49:35.248
my project would be able to store
that much electricity.

49:36.105 --> 49:39.009
Yeah, I kinda already
figured that out, thanks.

49:39.076 --> 49:41.385
But that got me thinking

49:41.445 --> 49:46.986
where under earth would I find
something or someone

49:47.050 --> 49:52.193
that is capable of absorbing
that much electricity?

49:52.522 --> 49:53.660
Hmm.

49:54.991 --> 49:56.061
Uh...

50:00.197 --> 50:04.236
You let Twyla go because you knew
she'd lead me down here.

50:04.301 --> 50:06.747
You need me to make your machine work.

50:07.104 --> 50:09.015
Yup. Hmph!

50:17.581 --> 50:19.288
No! Frankie!

50:30.060 --> 50:32.301
Testing. Testing one, two.

50:32.863 --> 50:34.604
Hello, Monster High!

50:34.664 --> 50:37.140
We are Howling Thunder and Frightening

50:37.200 --> 50:40.110
featuring Raythe and Deuce
and The Rolling Bones!

50:40.170 --> 50:41.171
And Woolee.

50:41.238 --> 50:43.445
Who wants to hear some heavy-ish metal

50:43.507 --> 50:48.388
monster alternative goth rock
with subtle undertones of smooth jazz?

50:51.548 --> 50:53.459
And there's some polka in there, too.

50:54.451 --> 50:55.486
Yeah!

50:55.552 --> 50:58.158
I said a one, a two, a one, two...

51:00.924 --> 51:03.400
Uh, guys, we never practiced any songs.

51:03.460 --> 51:05.269
Yeah, I was meaning to bring that up.

51:05.729 --> 51:06.833
Uh...

51:13.003 --> 51:14.004
Whoa!

51:14.571 --> 51:15.572
- Whoa!
- Whoa! What the...

51:15.639 --> 51:16.640
Huh?

51:16.873 --> 51:17.908
Ow! Hey!

51:19.409 --> 51:22.117
- Oh. What's all this, then?
- It's kinda cool!

51:22.779 --> 51:23.814
Nice!

51:24.548 --> 51:27.324
Hey! Where's my electric outfit?

51:38.828 --> 51:40.933
- Is there a blackout?
- What's going on?

51:56.846 --> 51:59.019
What... What?

51:59.082 --> 52:01.323
- Crikey.
- What should we do?

52:03.386 --> 52:04.524
- Excuse me.
- We should get out of here.

52:04.588 --> 52:05.658
Come on, you guys, let's go!

52:06.223 --> 52:08.198
Um, nothing to worry about, people!

52:08.258 --> 52:11.398
Just a little technical difficulty
on our first night.

52:11.461 --> 52:14.704
If I could direct your attention
to the table in the corner...

52:14.764 --> 52:17.574
Please help yourself to some refreshments.

52:20.670 --> 52:22.172
- Whoa!
- This is not okay!

52:41.157 --> 52:42.599
Frankie!

52:42.659 --> 52:45.196
She can't hear you!

53:31.041 --> 53:32.076
Uh...

53:56.299 --> 53:57.403
Huh?

54:10.280 --> 54:11.418
Hey!

54:11.481 --> 54:13.188
- What the...
- Moanica?

54:22.792 --> 54:23.827
Boo!

54:23.893 --> 54:25.429
Zombies! What's happening?

54:25.495 --> 54:26.936
I didn't get my hair done yet!

54:26.996 --> 54:28.634
Are you scared?

54:28.698 --> 54:29.938
Well, you should be!

54:29.999 --> 54:34.470
Because monsters and zombies are real!

54:34.537 --> 54:36.278
And tonight...

54:40.176 --> 54:44.020
Ugh! Will somebody please help him?
Por favor?

54:45.215 --> 54:49.823
And tonight, under the cover
of perpetual darkness,

54:49.886 --> 54:53.763
me and my Zomboys
are going out into your world.

54:53.823 --> 54:58.272
And we're going to do terrible,
scarible things!

54:58.628 --> 54:59.834
That's right!

54:59.896 --> 55:02.467
We're going to tie your shoelaces together!

55:02.532 --> 55:05.206
We're gonna put salt in your sugar bowls!

55:05.268 --> 55:08.943
We're gonna do a lot of this...

55:28.291 --> 55:30.897
That's right, run!

55:30.960 --> 55:36.467
Because this is the Night of the Zomboys!

55:36.533 --> 55:38.535
Moanica! What have you done?

55:44.707 --> 55:46.347
Moanica!

56:50.740 --> 56:53.016
Well, if you don't count the whole

56:53.076 --> 56:57.316
"zombies stealing the electricity
and falling through the floor" thing,

56:57.380 --> 56:59.987
I'd say tonight went pretty well.

57:01.451 --> 57:02.555
Ghouls!

57:02.619 --> 57:04.189
It's Frankie.

57:04.254 --> 57:05.494
Frankie?

57:06.289 --> 57:08.598
Frankie! What happened?

57:08.658 --> 57:11.798
It was Moanica!
She used Frankie for her plan!

57:12.228 --> 57:15.641
So much electricity.

57:15.965 --> 57:18.036
She's in shock!

57:18.101 --> 57:20.410
We have to get all that
electricity out of her.

57:20.470 --> 57:21.949
Znap! Znap!

57:23.406 --> 57:24.714
Znap!

57:26.809 --> 57:28.251
Znap!

57:28.311 --> 57:32.923
Frankie, whatever you did before
to make Znap, can you do it again?

57:39.722 --> 57:42.396
Znap, can you wake her?

57:42.458 --> 57:43.698
Znap?

57:44.928 --> 57:46.464
Znap, Znap!

57:49.566 --> 57:51.341
Znap, Znap...

57:54.470 --> 57:55.642
Znap.

57:58.241 --> 57:59.584
Znap, Znap!

58:01.444 --> 58:02.821
Znap?

58:10.086 --> 58:11.087
